The '''Nuruodo family''', also known as '''House Nuruodo''' or the '''Second Ruling Family''', was a [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] kin-group from [[Naporar/Legends|Naporar]], one of the [[Ruling Families/Legends|Ruling Families]] of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]]. It was responsible for foreign policy and military affairs, including the command of the [[Chiss Expansionary Defense Force]] and the Chiss military units known as [[Phalanx (Chiss)|Household]] and [[Phalanx (Chiss)|Colonial Phalanxes]].

==History==
According to a study produced by the [[University of Sanbra]] in the last years of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], the Nuruodo lineage was then one of four Ruling Families within the Chiss oligarchy. The results of this study indicated that they had oversight over military affairs and foreign policy, making them the second most important of the Families, after the [[Csapla family]]. It was believed that the majority of contact that outsiders had with the Chiss was with agents from the Nuruodo family.<ref name="USGIL:TC">{{GamerCite|5|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Chiss}}</ref>

During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Sev'eere'nuruodo]] was [[Aristocra/Legends|Aristocra]] of the family and met the young Chiss [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Nuru Kungurama]] in a diplomatic mission. [[Reproduction/Legends|Born]] by the name Kung'urama'nuruodo, Kungurama was a member of the Second Ruling Family himself, but was raised away from Chiss Space at the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="Curse of the Black Hole Pirates">''[[The Clone Wars: Secret Missions 2: Curse of the Black Hole Pirates]]''</ref> As an infant in [[33 BBY/Legends|33 BBY]],<ref name="The Essential Reader's Companion">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> Kungurama was placed alone in the [[Escape pod/Legends|escape pod]] of a Chiss [[Starship/Legends|ship]] with a [[Code cylinder|data cylinder]] identifying his name. He was found drifting alone by two Jedi<ref name="Curse of the Black Hole Pirates" /> whose [[translator droid]]s misread the data cylinder, thus christening him Nuru Kungurama.<ref name="Guardians of the Chiss Key">''[[The Clone Wars: Secret Missions 4: Guardians of the Chiss Key]]''</ref> He had no memory of his life among the Chiss and would have no contact with his family or any others of their [[Species/Legends|species]] until his encounter with Sev'eere'nuruodo eleven years later.<ref name="Curse of the Black Hole Pirates" />

